The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Bangla drop Kapali for Iqbal
 Alok Kapali Dhaka: Bangladesh have dropped middle order batsman Alok Kapali in favour of Nafis Iqbal in their 14-man squad for next months ICC Champions Trophy which starts in England on September 10. Middle order batsman Faisal Hossain and spinner Abdul Razzaq were both dropped to accommodate Aftab Ahmed, the Bangladesh Cricket Control Board said on Monday. Meanwhile, Former Kenya captain Maurice Odumbe, who is facing charges of dealing with a bookmaker, has been selected for next months Champions Trophy, adds another report from Nairobi. BANGLA SQUAD Habibul Bashar (captain), Rajin Saleh (vice-captain), Mohammad Ashraful, Javed Omar, Nafis Iqbal, Aftab Ahmed, Mushfiqur Rahman, Khaled Mahmud, Khaled Mashud, Mohammad Rafique, Manjurul Islam Rana, Tapash Baisya, Tareq Aziz, Nazmul Hossain. KENYA SQUAD Steve Tikolo (captain), Kennedy Obuya (vice-captain), Ravindu Shah, Hitesh Modi, Maurice Odumbe, Malhar Patel, Thomas Odoyo, Rageb Aga, Martin Suji, Peter Ongondo, Lamech Onyango, Tony Suji, Morris Auma and Josephat Ababu.  (REUTERS)  Copyright 
